@Autowired only takes effect when the object is handled by the spring context. As you said, the problem is that you created an object using the &#39;new&#39; operator, this object will be not handled by spring.
You have to use the application context. Also, the @Component default scope is singleton, add the annotation @Scope(&quot;prototype&quot;) to your Team component if you want to get a new object every time you call getBean().

Check if this code helps you.

    @Controller
    @RequestMapping(&quot;/teams&quot;)
    public class TeamsController {
        @Autowired
        private ApplicationContext appContext;
    
        @GetMapping(&quot;/new&quot;)
        public String createTeam(Model model) {
            model.addAttribute(&quot;team&quot;,appContext.getBean(Team.class));
            return &quot;/teams/create&quot;;
        }
    }

